This paper deals with the coexistence of Wi-Fi and LTE-U in shared or unlicensed bands, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI). The paper proposes a scheme to detect misbehavior in LTE-U duty cycling, which involves security and cryptography (CR) and information theory (IT). The proposed scheme is evaluated through simulations, which involves multimedia (MM) and systems and control (SY).
